# in __main__ block:
#
# ── Forward-only tests (no LLM required) ──
#
# 1. shape: st_attention output feeds st_moe, output shape == input shape
# 2. merged content detection: st_attention output elements contain kFrameMarker
# 3. causal 1x3: attention output has correct frame counts (1, 2, 3),
#    st_moe output has same shape [1, 3], all elements non-None
# 4. causal 1x5: frame count monotonically increases, coefficients match
# 5. full attention 1x4: all attention outputs have 4 frames each,
#    st_moe sees fully merged context per position
# 6. diagonal 1x3: each position attends only to self, 1 frame each,
#    st_moe gets plain-like content (single frame)
# 7. padding 1x4 (2 real + 2 pad): padded positions have coeff 0 after attention,
#    st_moe output reflects: real tokens translated, padded tokens empty
# 8. multi-batch 2x3 causal: independent attention per batch, both batches
#    produce valid merged content, st_moe processes each independently
# 9. multi-batch 3x2 mixed masks: causal/full/diagonal per batch,
#    different frame counts per batch, all pass through st_moe
# 10. coefficient propagation: attention coeff (frame count) propagated
#     correctly as st_moe input coefficients
# 11. content preservation: each frame in merged attention output
#     contains original input text (not corrupted by merge/unpack)
# 12. experience selection: st_moe selects topk experience entries
#     for each input element (including merged ones), verify selection count
# 13. storage consistency: no extra files in attention output or st_moe output,
#     coeff > 0 iff data file exists with non-zero size
#
# ── Backward tests (require LLM, simple tasks for high pass rate) ──
#
# 14. backward shape: full pipeline forward→backward, grad_input.shape == input.shape
# 15. backward produces symbolic content: grad_input elements are non-None diffs
# 16. merged backward detection: st_moe backward correctly detects merged
#     input and creates per-frame tasks (not one giant merged blob task)
# 17. plain vs merged mixed: tensor with both plain and merged elements,
#     backward handles both in single TaskHandler call
# 18. frame count preserved in backward: improved merged content after
#     backward has same number of frames as original
# 19. coefficient channel: grad_input numeric values match expected
#     (pass-through from grad_output)
# 20. causal 1x3 backward: typo fix propagates through attention+moe backward
# 21. multi-batch 2x2 backward: independent grad per batch through full pipeline
# 22. grad_experience shape: grad_experience matches experience tensor shape
# 23. grad_experience content: experience key/value gradients are non-None diffs
# 24. round-trip 1x3 causal: forward → manual modify output → backward →
#     verify grad_input has meaningful diffs for all attended positions
# 25. storage consistency backward: coeff-storage alignment in grad_input
#     and grad_experience after full backward
#
# ── End-to-end integration tests ──
#
# 26. two-iteration training loop: forward → backward → st_sgd step → forward again,
#     verify output changes between iterations
# 27. experience update: after backward + optimizer step, experience entries
#     are modified (not identical to initial)
# 28. attention mask change: same input with different masks produces
#     different st_moe outputs (attention actually affects downstream)
# 29. large batch 4x6 causal: stress test with realistic batch/seq_len,
#     all storage consistent, no crashes
# 30. sliding window 1x5 + st_moe: non-causal mask pattern,
#     verify merged frame counts match window size per position
